# Contributing to {{ project_name }}

Thanks for contributing. This project follows a light, reproducible workflow.

## Commit messages

Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/). The changelog
is generated from commit history, so the type prefix matters:

- `feat:` a new capability
- `fix:` a bug fix
- `docs:` documentation only
- `refactor:` code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
- `test:` adding or correcting tests
- `chore:` tooling, deps, or housekeeping

## Architecture decisions (ADRs)

Record any decision that changes how the project works as an ADR under
`docs/adr/`. Copy the existing template, give it the next number, and link it
from the relevant policy or the knowledge map. If a change reverses or
supersedes an earlier decision, note that in the new ADR.

## Do not run `/init`

A curated `CLAUDE.md` and `.claude/` governance layer already ship with the
project. Running `/init` would overwrite authored guidance. Edit the existing
files instead.

## Local checks

Run the same checks CI runs before opening a pull request:

```sh
make lint     # static analysis / style
make test     # the test or pipeline target
make check    # lint + test + placeholder scan
```

Fix any findings before pushing.

## Pulling template updates (optional)

This project was generated with [copier](https://copier.readthedocs.io). To pull
later improvements from the template:

```sh
copier update
```

Review the diff, re-run `make check`, and re-run `/psotobverse-utils:sync-cowork` if the
constitution or policies changed.
